  "text": "Sequence diversity in different HIV-1 subtypes may influence the emergence of drug resistance mutations. K65R may be more likely to develop in subtype C, due to the nucleic acid variation surrounding this codon [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The overall impact of HIV-1 genetic diversity on transmission of resistance is unclear.",
